name: Apple buys Israeli startup Q.ai as the AI race heats up
description: Q.ai is an Israeli startup specializing in imaging and machine learning, particularly technologies that enable devices to interpret whispered speech and enhance audio in noisy environments.

name: Upwind raises $250M at $1.5B valuation to continue building ‘runtime’ cloud security
description: The $250 million Series B was led by Bessemer Venture Partners, with participation from Salesforce Ventures and Picture Capital.

name: SpaceX is coming to the public markets, and secondaries are already on fire
description: paceX is reportedly lining up four major Wall Street banks for a 2026 IPO that could provide the reset the market needs.  The company just completed a tender offer at an $800 billion valuation, and secondary market demand is through the roof. name: AI security startup Outtake raises $40M from Iconiq, Satya Nadella, Bill Ackman, and other big names
description: Outtake makes an agentic cybersecurity platform to help enterprises detect identity fraud. Its angel investors read like a who's who of tech industry names.

name: The SpaceX IPO could finally happen (and it’s a big deal)
description: SpaceX is reportedly lining up four major Wall Street banks for a 2026 IPO that could provide the reset the market needs.  The company just completed a tender offer at an $800 billion valuation, and secondary market demand is through the roof. name: Jennifer Garner’s Once Upon a Farm resumes IPO plans
description: The organic kids' snack food company may debut as soon as next week. It has issued a price range for shares, an SEC filing shows.

name: AI data labeler Handshake buys  Cleanlab, an acquisition target of multiple others
description: The deal’s purpose is primarily to acquire talent, aka an acqui-hire, adding nine key Cleanlab employees to Handshake’s research organization.

name: Tiny startup Arcee AI built a 400B-parameter open source LLM from scratch to best Meta’s Llama
description: 30-person startup Arcee AI has released a 400B model called Trinity, which it says is one of the biggest open source foundation models from a U.S. company.

name: TechCrunch Disrupt 2026: Plus-one passes are almost gone and only 3 days remain
description: The TechCrunch Disrupt 2026 plus-one passes at 50% off are almost sold out, and this deal ends in 3 days. Register here before this deal ends on Friday, January 30 at 11:59 p.m. PT.

name: The conference where founders scale: TechCrunch Founder Summit 2026 tickets are now live at the lowest prices
description: TechCrunch Founder Summit 2026 unites 1,100 founders and investors in Boston on June 23 for a day focused on real-world scaling insights and networking that pushes the needle. Save up to $300 on your ticket.

name: Redwood attracts Google for its $425M Series E as AI power needs rise
description: Google is the latest investor to back Redwood Materials as the battery recycling startup scales a new energy storage venture to power AI data centers and other industrial sites.

name: Fashion rental app By Rotation and Uber partner to help deliver ski clothing
description: By Rotation, one of the U.K.’s most popular peer-to-peer fashion rental platforms, is partnering with Uber to deliver ski clothes.

name: Anduril has invented a wild new drone-flying contest where jobs are the prize
description: This is a race series for software programmers and the brainchild of founder Palmer Luckey, he tells TechCrunch.

name: Anthropic reportedly upped its latest raise to $20B
description: Anthropic looks to raise $20 billion at more than $300 billion valuation, according to reports.

name: Northwood Space secures a $100M Series B and a $50M Space Force contract
description: With so much interest in funding space tech, hard tech, and defense tech right now, Mendler said this was an opportunity for her company to grow responsibly and quickly.

name: Qualcomm backs SpotDraft to scale on-device contract AI with valuation doubling toward $400M
description: SpotDraft now processes over 1 million contracts annually using its AI tool, with contract volumes up 173% year-over-year.

name: South Korea’s Edenlux set for US debut of eye-strain wellness device
description: Edenlux builds wearable tech to protect and train your eyes, inspired by its founder’s personal vision recovery.

name: AI chip startup Ricursive hits $4B valuation 2 months after launch
description: Ricursive joins Recursive and Unconventional AI in raising massive funds at multibillion-dollar valuations out of the gate.

name: AI startup CVector raises $5M for its industrial ‘nervous system’
description: Now, founders Richard Zhang and Tyler Ruggles are tasked with a bigger challenge: showing customers and investors how this AI-powered software layer translates to real savings on an industrial scale.

name: Only 5 days left: Over half of the first 500 TechCrunch Disrupt 2026 plus-one passes at 50% off are already gone
description: Register now to save up to $680 on your TechCrunch Disrupt 2026 pass and get a +1 ticket at 50% off. Offer ends this Friday, January 30.

name: Vinod Khosla publicly disavows Keith Rabois’ comments on ICE shooting
description: Unwavering Trump loyalist and VC Keith Rabois caused his colleague  and his firm's founder to distance themselves from his comments on ICE.

name: Obvious Ventures lands fund five with a 360-degree view of planetary, human, economic health
description: The 12-year-old firm raised $360,360,360 for its fifth fund. And there's a reason for that number.

name: VC firm 2150 raises €210M fund to solve cities’ climate challenges
description: Europe-based venture fund 2150 raised the money to invest in climate tech startups that help solve cities' carbon footprint.

name: What is Bending Spoons? The little-known firm behind Vimeo’s sweeping layoffs
description: Bending Spoons remains largely unknown, even as its portfolio of products has served more than a billion people.

name: Only 1 week left (or until the first 500 passes are gone): The first TechCrunch Disrupt 2026 ticket discount is ending
description: Register now to save up to $680 on your TechCrunch Disrupt 2026 pass and get a second ticket at 50% off. This offer ends next week on January 30, or once the first 500 tickets are claimed — whichever comes first.

name: Former Sequoia partner’s new startup uses AI to negotiate your calendar for you
description: Blockit, an AI agent that communicates directly with other calendars, has raised $5 million in seed funding led by Sequoia.

name: Voice AI engine and OpenAI partner LiveKit hits $1B valuation
description: The five-year-old-startup powers OpenAI’s ChatGPT voice mode and raised a $100 million round led by Index Ventures.

name: Inference startup Inferact lands $150M to commercialize vLLM
description: The seed round values the newly formed startup at $800 million.

name: Former CEO of celeb fav gym Dogpound launches $5M fund to back wellness companies
description: Jenny Liu is a solo first-time GP looking to back underrepresented wellness founders.

name: Sources: Project SGLang spins out as RadixArk with $400M valuation as inference market explodes
description: SGLang, which originated as an open source research project at Ion Stoica’s UC Berkeley lab, has raised capital from Accel.

name: Zipline charts drone delivery expansion with $600M in new funding
description: That geographic expansion in the United States has fueled Zipline’s delivery numbers. In 2024, the company completed 1 million drone deliveries to customers; this week, Zipline said it had surpassed 2 million deliveries.

name: OpenAI’s former sales leader joins VC firm Acrew: OpenAI taught her where startups can build a ‘moat’
description: Aliisa Rosenthal has found a new career as a VC. She knows what startups can do to protect themselves from the model makers eating their markets.

name: TechCrunch Disrupt 2026 tickets now on sale: Lowest rates all year
description: TechCrunch Disrupt 2026 tickets are officially on sale. Save up to $680 on your ticket and be among the first 500 registrants to score a plus-one pass at 50% off. Don't miss 10,000 tech leaders, founders, and VCs in San Francisco from October 13-15. Register before these one-time deals vanish.

name: PraxisPro raises $6M seed from AlleyCorp to coach medical sales reps
description: PraxisPro, founded by a former pharma sales rep, offers small language model AI training specifically designed for medical product sales.

name: One-time hot insurance tech Ethos poised to be one of the first tech IPO of the year
description: Ethos was backed by a who's who of VCs and celebs through 2021. It is currently profitable, it says.

name: Working in orbit: What happens when space goes blue collar?
description: In this episode of StrictlyVC Download, Connie Loizos speaks with Mary-Jane Rubenstein, a professor of religion and science and technology studies at Wesleyan University and author of “Worlds Without End: The Many Lives of the Multiverse” — a book that served as research material for the Oscar-winni

name: Retail startup Another raises a $2.5M seed to help sell excess inventory
description: Another hopes to help companies address excess inventory before brands opt to sell items to bulk resellers. Corina Marshall, Another's founder, says items sold through such resellers may be deeply discounted, an outcome brands might not want.
